Linux Commands:
ls // listing directory contents
cd // changing the working directory
cd .. // move backwards to prev. dir.
mkdir // make directory
rmdir // remove directory
touch // create empty file (imbue life)
rm <file> // remove file
gedit <filename> & // run gedit in terminal
sudo startunity -X xorg
javac <ClassName>.java // compile .java file
java <ClassName> // run class (program)

public class One {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.print("Hello");
    System.out.println("World");
  }
}

Output:
HelloWorld

// imagine ln means put a line at the end of whatever follows
